Founder%20Julian%20Assange's%20Legal%20Battles%3A%20A%20Timeline%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWikiLeaks%20founder%20Julian%20Assange%20has%20reached%20a%20deal%20to%20plead%20guilty%20to%20one%20count%20of%20violating%20the%20U.S.%20espionage%20law%2C%20prosecutors%20said%20in%20court%20papers%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20due%20to%20appear%20in%20a%20U.S.%20federal%20court%20in%20the%20Northern%20Mariana%20Islands%20this%20week%20where%20he%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20sentenced%20to%20time%20served%20and%20allowed%20to%20return%20home%20to%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20are%20some%20key%20events%20and%20details%20in%20Assange's%20life%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJuly%201971%20-%20Assange%20is%20born%20in%20Townsville%2C%20Australia%2C%20to%20parents%20involved%20in%20theatre.%20As%20a%20teenager%2C%20he%20gains%20a%20reputation%20as%20a%20computer%20programmer.%20In%201995%2C%20he%20is%20fined%20for%20computer%20hacking%20but%20avoids%20prison%20on%20condition%20he%20does%20not%20offend%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2006%20-%20Assange%20founds%20WikiLeaks%2C%20creating%20an%20internet-based%20%26quot%3Bdead%20letter%20drop%26quot%3B%20for%20leakers%20of%20classified%20or%20sensitive%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApril%205%2C%202010%20-%20WikiLeaks%20releases%20leaked%20video%20from%20a%20U.S.%20helicopter%20showing%20an%20air%20strike%20that%20killed%20civilians%20in%20Baghdad%2C%20including%20two%20Reuters%20news%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJuly%2025%2C%202010%20-%20WikiLeaks%20releases%20more%20than%2091%2C000%20documents%2C%20mostly%20secret%20U.S.%20military%20reports%20about%20the%20Afghanistan%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOctober%2C%202010%20-%20WikiLeaks%20releases%20400%2C000%20classified%20military%20files%20chronicling%20the%20Iraq%20war.%20The%20next%20month%2C%20it%20releases%20thousands%20of%20U.S.%20diplomatic%20cables%2C%20including%20candid%20views%20of%20foreign%20leaders%20and%20blunt%20assessments%20of%20security%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENov.%2018%2C%202010%20-%20A%20Swedish%20court%20orders%20Assange's%20arrest%20on%20sex%20crime%20allegations%2C%20which%20he%20denies.%20He%20is%20arrested%20in%20Britain%20the%20next%20month%20on%20a%20European%20arrest%20warrant%20but%20freed%20on%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFebruary%202011%20-%20London's%20Westminster%20Magistrates'%20Court%20orders%20Assange's%20extradition%20to%20Sweden.%20He%20appeals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJune%2014%2C%202012%20-%20The%20British%20Supreme%20Court%20rejects%20Assange's%20final%20appeal.%20Five%20days%20later%2C%20he%20takes%20refuge%20in%20Ecuador's%20embassy%20in%20London%20and%20seeks%20political%20asylum%2C%20which%20Ecuador%20grants%20in%20August%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMay%2019%2C%202017%20-%20Swedish%20prosecutors%20discontinue%20their%20investigation%2C%20saying%20it%20is%20impossible%20to%20proceed%20while%20Assange%20is%20in%20the%20Ecuadorean%20embassy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApril%2011%2C%202019%20-%20After%20Ecuador%20revokes%20his%20political%20asylum%2C%20Assange%20is%20carried%20out%20of%20the%20embassy%20and%20arrested.%20He%20is%20sentenced%20on%20May%201%20to%2050%20weeks%20in%20prison%20by%20a%20British%20court%20for%20skipping%20bail.%20He%20completes%20the%20sentence%20early%20but%20remains%20in%20jail%20pending%20extradition%20hearings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMay%2013%2C%202019%20-%20Swedish%20prosecutors%20reopen%20their%20investigation%20and%20say%20they%20will%20seek%20Assange's%20extradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJune%2011%2C%202019%20-%20The%20U.S.%20Justice%20Department%20formally%20asks%20Britain%20to%20extradite%20Assange%20to%20the%20United%20States%20to%20face%20charges%20that%20he%20conspired%20to%20hack%20U.S.%20government%20computers%20and%20violated%20an%20espionage%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENov.%2019%2C%202019%20-%20Swedish%20prosecutors%20drop%20their%20investigation%2C%20saying%20the%20evidence%20is%20not%20strong%20enough%20to%20bring%20charges%2C%20in%20part%20because%20of%20the%20passage%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFeb.%2021%2C%202020%20-%20A%20London%20court%20begins%20the%20first%20part%20of%20extradition%20hearings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJan.%204%2C%202021%20-%20A%20British%20judge%20rules%20that%20Assange%20should%20not%20be%20extradited%20to%20the%20U.S.%20to%20face%20criminal%20charges%2C%20saying%20his%20mental%20health%20problems%20mean%20he%20would%20be%20at%20risk%20of%20suicide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDec.%2010%2C%202021%20-%20The%20U.S.%20wins%20an%20appeal%20against%20the%20ruling%20after%20a%20judge%20says%20he%20is%20satisfied%20with%20a%20U.S.%20package%20of%20assurances%20about%20the%20conditions%20of%20Assange's%20detention.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarch%2014%2C%202022%20-%20Britain's%20Supreme%20Court%20denies%20Assange%20permission%20to%20appeal%20against%20the%20decision%20to%20extradite%20him%20to%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarch%2023%2C%202022%20-%20Assange%20marries%20his%20long-term%20partner%20Stella%20Moris%2C%20the%20mother%20of%20his%20two%20children%20fathered%20inside%20the%20Ecuadorean%20embassy%2C%20inside%20a%20British%20high-security%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJune%2017%2C%202022%20-%20Britain%20orders%20Assange's%20extradition%20to%20the%20United%20States%2C%20prompting%20Assange%20to%20appeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJune%2C%202023%20-%20Judge%20at%20London's%20High%20Court%20rules%20Assange%20has%20no%20legal%20grounds%20to%20appeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFeb.%2020%2C%202024%20-%20Assange%20launches%20what%20his%20supporters%20say%20will%20be%20his%20final%20attempt%20to%20prevent%20extradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarch%2026%2C%202024%20-%20The%20extradition%20is%20put%20on%20hold%20when%20the%20court%20says%20the%20U.S.%20must%20provide%20assurances%20that%20Assange%20will%20not%20face%20a%20potential%20death%20penalty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMay%2020%2C%202024%20-%20The%20High%20Court%20gives%20Assange%20permission%20to%20launch%20a%20full%20appeal%20against%20his%20