blishing%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20leaked%20US%20military%20documents%20about%20the%20wars%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%2C%20some%20of%20which%20detail%20US%20abuses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20later%20follows%20up%20with%20a%20huge%20batch%20of%20secret%20US%20diplomatic%20cables%2C%20which%20show%20that%20Washington%20spied%20on%20the%20leadership%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20and%20that%20Saudi%20Arabia%20pressured%20the%20US%20to%20attack%20Iran%2C%20among%20other%20revelations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%20that%20year%2C%20a%20Swedish%20prosecutor%20issues%20an%20arrest%20warrant%20for%20Assange%20over%20sexual%20assault%20allegations%20involving%20two%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssange%20denies%20the%20claims%2C%20saying%20they%20had%20consensual%20sex%2C%20but%20is%20arrested%20after%20he%20reports%20to%20police%20in%20London.%20A%20week%20later%20he%20is%20released%20on%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E2012%3A%20Embassy%20refuge%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202011%2C%20a%20British%20judge%20rules%20Assange%20can%20be%20extradited%20to%20Sweden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20appeals%2C%20claiming%20the%20Swedish%20allegations%20are%20a%20pretext%20to%20transfer%20him%20to%20the%20US%20to%20face%20charges%20over%20Wikileaks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20June%202012%2C%20he%20takes%20refuge%20in%20Ecuador's%20embassy%20in%20London.%20Ecuador%2C%20then%20ruled%20by%20left-wing%20president%20Rafael%20Correa%2C%20grants%20him%20asylum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202017%2C%20Swedish%20prosecutors%20drop%20the%20sex%20assault%20investigation%20after%20failing%20to%20obtain%20Assange's%20transfer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20December%2C%20Ecuador%20grants%20Assange%20nationality%20but%20is%20blocked%20by%20Britain%20from%20according%20him%20diplomatic%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E2019%3A%20Arrest%2C%20prison%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202018%2C%20Ecuador%2C%20now%20ruled%20by%20conservative%20President%20Lenin%20Moreno%2C%20says%20hosting%20Assange%20has%20become%20%26quot%3Buntenable%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETensions%20peak%20in%20April%202019%20when%20Moreno%20says%20Assange%20has%20%26quot%3Brepeatedly%20violated%26quot%3B%20the%20conditions%20of%20his%20asylum%20and%20revokes%20his%20citizenship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20day%2C%20British%20police%20drag%20Assange%20from%20the%20embassy%20and%20arrest%20him%20on%20a%20US%20extradition%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20he%20is%20sentenced%20to%2050%20weeks%20in%20jail%20for%20having%20breached%20bail%20in%202010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20legal%20process%20for%20his%20extradition%20to%20the%20US%20begins.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Swedish%20prosecutors%20reopen%20the%20rape%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EUS%20charges%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202019%2C%20the%20US%20Justice%20Department%20charges%20Assange%20with%20violating%20the%20US%20Espionage%20Act%20by%20publishing%20military%20and%20diplomatic%20files%20in%202010.%20If%20convicted%2C%20he%20faces%20jail%20terms%20of%20up%20to%20175%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssange%20makes%20his%20first%20court%20appearance%20since%20being%20jailed%20via%20video-link.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ESwedish%20charge%20dropped%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202019%2C%20Swedish%20prosecutors%20drop%20the%20rape%20investigation%20because%20%26quot%3Bthe%20evidence%20is%20not%20strong%20enough%26quot%3B%20despite%20%26quot%3Bcredible%26quot%3B%20claims%20from%20Assange's%20alleged%20victim.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E-%202020%3A%20Trump%20claim%20-%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202020%20court%20hearings%2C%20Assange's%20lawyers%20claim%20then%20US%20president%20Donald%20Trump%20had%20promised%20him%20a%20pardon%20if%20he%20denied%20Russia%20had%20leaked%20him%20damaging%20emails%20about%20Hillary%20Clinton%20ahead%20of%20the%202016%20presidential%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20denies%20the%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E2021%3A%20Victory%2C%20then%20setback%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssange's%20supporters%20celebrate%20after%20a%20London%20court%20blocks%20his%20extradition%20in%20January%202021%2C%20on%20the%20grounds%20he%20would%20be%20a%20suicide%20risk%20if%20sent%20to%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20High%20Court%20appeal%20overturns%20the%20verdict%20and%20sends%20the%20case%20back%20to%20the%20original%20court%20after%20a%20US%20promise%20he%20would%20not%20be%20held%20in%20isolation%20in%20jail%20and%20would%20receive%20proper%20medical%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E2022%3A%20Permission%20to%20appeal%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJudges%20in%20January%202022%20grant%20Assange%20permission%20to%20appeal.%20But%20in%20March%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20refuses%20to%20hear%20the%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2017%2C%202022%2C%20the%20British%20government%20approves%20his%20extradition%20in%20what%20Wikileaks%20calls%20a%20%26quot%3Bdark%20day%20for%20press%20freedom%20and%20for%20British%20democracy%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssange%20appeals%20the%20government's%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E'He%20will%20die'%20if%20extradited%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssange's%20wife%20Stella%20tells%20a%20news%20conference%20in%20February%202024%20that%20her%20husband%20%26quot%3Bwill%20die%26quot%3B%20if%20sent%20to%20the%20US%2C%20saying%20his%20physical%20and%20mental%20health%20are%20%26quot%3Bin%20decline%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20Assange%20wins%20permission%20to%20appeal%20against%20the%202022%20court%20ruling%20that%20approved%20his%20extradition%2C%20with%20a%20two-day%20hearing%20in%20London%20later%20scheduled%20for%20July%209.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E2024%3A%20Plea%20deal%20and%20release%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssange%20agrees%20