eral%20judges%20in%20Kansas%20and%20Missouri%20blocked%20student-loan%20forgiveness%20and%20cheaper%20payments%20through%20the%20SAVE%20plan.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20range%20of%20SAVE%20provisions%20set%20to%20go%20into%20effect%20July%201%20are%20now%20halted.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBorrowers%20can%20still%20remain%20on%20the%20SAVE%20plan%20as%20the%20legal%20process%20continues.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden's%20new%20student-loan%20repayment%20plan%20just%20got%20dealt%20two%20blows%20by%20federal%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20judges%20in%20Kansas%20and%20Missouri%20district%20courts%20handed%20down%20their%20rulings%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgop-states-lawsuit-block-save-student-loan-income-driven-repayment-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwo%20separate%20lawsuits%3C%2Fa%3E%20filed%20by%20GOP%20state%20attorneys%20general%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-blocked-save-plan-lawsuit-gop-attorneys-general-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseeking%20to%20block%20the%20SAVE%20income-driven%20repayment%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20introduced%20last%20summer%20to%20lower%20borrowers'%20monthly%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20the%20Education%20Department%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-debt-cancellation-save-income-driven-payment-plan-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimplementing%20a%20SAVE%20provision%20ahead%20of%20schedule%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20canceled%20student%20debt%20for%20borrowers%20with%20original%20balances%20of%20%2412%2C000%20or%20less%20who%20made%20as%20few%20as%2010%20years%20of%20qualifying%20payments.%20The%20attorneys%20general%20argued%20that%20relief%20was%20unconstitutional%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20and%20requested%20the%20relief%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20plan%20overall%20%E2%80%94%20be%20blocked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Missouri%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.moed.211135%2Fgov.uscourts.moed.211135.35.0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eruled%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20one%20of%20the%20lawsuits%20led%20by%20Missouri%20Attorney%20General%20Andrew%20Bailey%20that%20the%20Education%20Department%20can%20no%20longer%20carry%20out%20student-loan%20forgiveness%20via%20SAVE%20as%20the%20legal%20process%20continues.%20The%20ruling%20still%20preserves%20borrowers'%20abilities%20to%20enroll%20and%20make%20payments%20through%20the%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20borrowers%20have%20already%20made%20payments%20under%20the%20program%2C%20have%20already%20had%20those%20payments%20calculated%20under%20the%20early%20implementation%20of%20certain%20provisions%20of%20the%20Final%20Rule%2C%20and%20some%20borrowers%20anticipate%20imminent%20forgiveness%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20ruling%20stated.%20%26quot%3BThese%20borrowers%20and%20the%20public%20have%20an%20interest%20in%20ensuring%20consistency%20in%20loan%20repayment%20programs%2C%20and%20any%20preliminary%20injunction%20would%20harm%20their%20expectations%20of%20such%20consistency.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Education%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Kansas%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.ksd.151881%2Fgov.uscourts.ksd.151881.76.0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eruled%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20would%20preserve%20actions%20the%20Education%20Department%20has%20already%20implemented%20through%20the%20SAVE%20plan%2C%20but%20it%20will%20halt%20the%20new%20provisions%20set%20to%20go%20into%20effect%20on%20July%201%2C%20including%20cutting%20payments%20for%20undergraduate%20borrowers%20in%20half.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKansas'%20ruling%20will%20go%20into%20effect%20on%20June%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20of%20the%20rulings%20are%20preliminary%2C%20and%20while%20student-loan%20forgiveness%20is%20blocked%20for%20the%20time%20being%2C%20courts%20have%20yet%20to%20hand%20down%20their%20final%20rulings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMike%20Pierce%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20advocacy%20group%20Student%20Borrower%20Protection%20Center%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20%26quot%3Bmillions%20of%20borrowers%20are%20now%20in%20limbo%20as%20they%20struggle%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20their%20rights%20under%20the%20law%20and%20the%20information%20being%20provided%20by%20the%20government%20and%20their%20student%20loan%20companies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAre%20borrowers'%20bills%20accurate%3F%20Are%20interest%20charges%20correct%3F%20Will%20the%20amount%20due%20today%20be%20the%20same%20due%20tomorrow%3F%20Will%20borrowers'%20promised%20cancellation%20still%20receive%20critical%20relief%3F%20These%20basic%2C%20essential%20questions%20have%20no%20answers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudge%20Daniel%20Crabtree%2C%20who%20delivered%20the%20Kansas%20ruling%2C%20was%20previously%20skeptical%20of%20the%20GOP%20attorneys%20general's%20case%20and%20ruled%20on%20June%207%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-gop-block-save-plan-standing-just-barely-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejust%20three%20of%20the%20original%20eleven%20states%20had%20standing%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20challenge%20the%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20these%20two%20rulings%20are%20setbacks%20for%20borrowers%20who%20were%20hoping%20to%20benefit%20from%20the%20SAVE%20plan%20that%20the%20Education%20Department%20has%20been%20touting%20for%20the%20past%20year.%20While%20the%20department%20continues%20to%20carry%20out%20separate%20relief%20for%20borrowers%20through%20one-time%20account%20adjustments%2C%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-announces-new-student-loan-forgiveness-plan-who-qualifies-relief-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebroader%20plan%20for%20debt%20cancellation%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20expected%20to%20benefit%20over%2030%20million%20borrowers%20%E2%80%94%20is%20highly%20likely%20to%20encounter%20legal%20challenges%20this%20fall%2C%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKansas%20and%20Missouri's%20attorneys%20general%20celebrated%20the%20rulings.%20Kansas'%20Attorney%20General%20Kris%20Kobach%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FKSAGOffice%2Fstatus%2F1805357027243303093%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20X%20that%20%26quot%3BKansas's%20victory%20today%20is%20a%20victory%20for%20the%20entire%20country.%20As%20the%20court%20correctly%20held%2C%20whether%20to%20forgive%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20student%20debt%20is%20a%20major%20question%20that%20only%20Congress%20can%20answer.%20Biden's%20administration%20is%20attempting%20to%20usurp%20Congress's%20authority.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-blocked-lower-monthly-payments-save-plan-courts-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719271142000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6679eb0ed1c84a0eaca75d74%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-blocked-lower-monthly-payments-save-plan-courts-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Two%20separate%20rulings%20from%20federal%20judges%20in%20Kansas%20and%20Missouri%20halted%20student-debt%20cancellation%20and%20lower%20payments%20through%20the%20SAVE%20plan.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A89%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-blocked-lower-monthly-payments-save-plan-courts-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title