22%3A%22Netflix%20just%20tweaked%20its%20famous%20'keeper%20test'%20used%20to%20drive%20out%20underperformers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226811%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Netflix%20executives%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6679d51c50b021b5cae8f14b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224541%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENetflix%20executives%20with%20co-CEO%20Greg%20Peters%20in%20the%20center.%20%3Cp%3EDavid%20Becker%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-netflix-is-changing-the-entertainment-industry-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENetflix%3C%2Fa%3E%20added%20a%20new%20line%20about%20its%20%26quot%3Bkeeper%20test%26quot%3B%20in%20an%20updated%20version%20of%20its%20culture%20memo.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20test%20is%20when%20a%20manager%20asks%20themselves%20if%20they%20would%20fight%20to%20keep%20an%20employee.%20If%20the%20answer%20is%20no%2C%20they're%20fired.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENetflix's%20culture%20deck%20is%20famous%20in%20the%20corporate%20world%20for%20its%20directness%20in%20stating%20company%20values.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENetflix%20overhauled%20its%20famous%20culture%20memo%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20means%20a%20new%20line%20added%20about%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetflix-ceo-reed-hastings-used-keeper-test-to-fire-product-chief-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bkeeper%20test%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20used%20by%20managers%20to%20determine%20if%20they%20should%20fire%20an%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20keeper%20test%20was%20previously%20defined%20as%20when%20a%20manager%20asks%20%26quot%3BIf%20a%20team%20member%20was%20leaving%20for%20a%20similar%20role%20at%20another%20company%2C%20would%20the%20manager%20try%20to%20keep%20them%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20answer%20was%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20employee%20was%20given%20generous%20severance%20and%20cut%20so%20that%20a%20stronger%20replacement%20could%20be%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENetflix%20has%20long%20been%20known%20to%20operate%20its%20business%20like%20a%20sports%20team%2C%20not%20a%20family%2C%20and%20the%20keeper%20test%20is%20part%20of%20that%20culture.%20This%20also%20means%20tenures%20can%20be%20brief%20as%20the%20company%20seeks%20out%20top%20talent%20and%20is%20quick%20to%20cut%20underperformers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20keeper%20test%20has%20since%20evolved%20to%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20X%20wanted%20to%20leave%2C%20would%20I%20fight%20to%20keep%20them%3F%26quot%3B%20Or%2C%20%26quot%3BKnowing%20everything%20I%20know%20today%2C%20would%20I%20hire%20X%20again%3F%26quot%3B%20If%20the%20answer%20is%20no%2C%20the%20memo%20says%20it's%20fairer%20for%20everyone%20to%20part%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20same%20idea%20just%20worded%20a%20bit%20differently%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20also%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjobs.netflix.com%2Fculture%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincludes%20a%20disclaimer%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20abstract%2C%20the%20keeper%20test%20can%20sound%20scary%2C%26quot%3B%20Netflix%20says%20in%20the%20latest%20version%20of%20its%20culture%20memo.%20%26quot%3BIn%20reality%2C%20we%20encourage%20everyone%20to%20speak%20to%20their%20managers%20about%20what's%20going%20well%20and%20what's%20not%20on%20a%20regular%20basis.%20This%20helps%20avoid%20surprises.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20the%20abstract%2C%20the%20keeper%20test%20can%20sound%20scary.%20In%20reality%2C%20we%20encourage%20everyone%20to%20speak%20to%20their%20managers%20about%20what's%20going%20well%20and%20what's%20not%20on%20a%20regular%20basis.%20This%20helps%20avoid%20surprises.%20Managers%20also%20evaluate%20team%20members%20on%20their%20whole%20record%2C%20rather%20than%20focusing%20on%20the%20mistakes%20or%20bets%20that%20didn't%20pay%20off.%20On%20the%20Dream%20Team%2C%20you%20need%20people%20who%20challenge%20the%20status%20quo%20and%20try%20new%20things.%20So%20we%20stick%20with%20employees%20through%20short-term%20bumps.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3ENetflix's%20keeper%20test%20was%20first%20introduced%20in%20an%20over%20100-page%20memo%20published%20in%202009.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetflix-reed-hastings-company-culture-big-tech-severance-candor-performance-2024-4%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNetflix%2520encourages%2520its%2520managers%2520to%2Cbe%2520fine%2520with%2520them%2520departing.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENetflix%20used%20to%20encourage%20managers%20to%20do%20the%20test%3C%2Fa%3E%20once%20per%20quarter%2C%20founder%20and%20former%20CEO%20Reed%20Hastings%20said.%20He%20reportedly%20used%20it%20to%20fire%20his%20product%20chief%20and%20longtime%20friend%20after%2018%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20memo%2C%20which%20was%20originally%20regarded%20as%20fairly%20blunt%20for%20a%20public%20corporate%20document%2C%20has%20had%20several%20revisions%20since%20it%20was%20first%20released%20and%20is%20now%20only%20five%20pages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENetflix%20co-CEO%20Greg%20Peters%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F24182520%2Fnetflix-co-ceo-memo-ads-subscription-price-decoder-podcast-interview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20an%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20The%20Verge's%20%26quot%3BDecoder%26quot%3B%20podcast%20that%20the%20memo%20is%20shorter%20because%20the%20company%20got%20%26quot%3Bbetter%20at%20articulating%26quot%3B%20its%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20interview%20published%20Monday%2C%20Peters%20said%20that%20the%20original%20memo%20may%20have%20also%20incorrectly%20communicated%20that%20Netflix%20%26quot%3Bwas%20a%20harsh%20and%20maybe%20cutthroat%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20he%20said%20it%20isn't.%20In%20the%20three%20versions%20after%2C%20Peters%20said%20the%20company%20may%20have%20swung%20too%20far%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20pendulum%20and%20went%20too%20soft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20co-CEO%20said%20that%20in%20the%20versions%20that%20followed%20the%20original%2C%20employees%20also%20misinterpreted%20the%20company's%20statement%20on%20%26quot%3Bfreedom%20and%20responsibility%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20which%20essentially%20said%20Netflix%20employees%20were%20trusted%20to%20act%20in%20the%20company's%20best%20interest%20and%20weren't%20micro-managed%20%E2%80%94%20and%20acted%20in%20ways%20that%20weren't%20in%20line%20with%20its%20collective%20corporate%20goals.%20It%20has%20since%20deleted%20that%20section%20and%20its%20new%20section%2C%20%26quot%3BPeople%20Over%20Process%2C%26quot%3B%20includes%20a%20statement%20about%20hiring%20%26quot%3Bunusually%20responsible%20people%20who%20thrive%20on%20this%20openness%20and%20freedom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20memo%20also%20says%20%26quot%3BNot%20all%20opinions%20are%20created%20equal%26quot%3B%20and%20that%2C%20as%20the%20company%20has%20grown%2C%20it's%20no%20longer%20possible%20for%20everyone%20to%20weigh%20in%20on%20every%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20memo%20took%2012%20months%20to%20make%20and%20received%201%2C500%20comments%20from%20employees%20weighing%20in%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabout.netflix.com%2Fen%2Fnews%2Fsharing-our-latest-culture-memo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20a%20press%20release%20from%20Netflix.%20It%20was%20made%20publicly%20available%20on%20June%2024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20read%20the%20newest%20version%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjobs.netflix.com%2Fculture%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENetflix's%20culture%20memo%20here.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetflix-new-culture-memo-keeper-test-changes-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719264902000%2C%22visual%22%3A%2